The paper discusses a method for modeling variability in component-based software systems, which is a topic that falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions product line development, which is a subfield of software product line engineering (cs.PL). The use of a meta model to formalize the conceptual ideas suggests a focus on software design (cs.SD). The paper also mentions tool support, which could indicate a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for developing such tools.
